
[1]assess

   ASSESS', v.t. [L. assideo, ad and sedeo.]

   1. To set, fix or charge a certain sum upon one, as a tax; as, to
   assess each citizen in due proportion.

   2. To value; to fix the value of property, for the purpose of being
   taxed; as by the law of the United States. Also, to value or fix the
   profits of business, for the purpose of taxation.

   3. To set, fix or ascertain; as, it is the province of a jury to assess
   damages.

                     ASSESS', n. Assessment. [Not used.]
